186 enum class value_t : uint8_t {
187  null,
188  object,
189  array,
190  string,
191  boolean,
192  number_integer,
193  number_unsigned,
194  number_float,
195  discarded
196 };
197 
207 inline bool operator<(const value_t lhs, const value_t rhs) noexcept {
208  static constexpr std::array<uint8_t, 8> order = {{
209  0, // null
210  3, // object
211  4, // array
212  5, // string
213  1, // boolean
214  2, // integer
215  2, // unsigned
216  2, // float
217  }};
218 
219  // discarded values are not comparable
220  if (lhs == value_t::discarded or rhs == value_t::discarded) {
221  return false;
222  }
223 
224  return order[static_cast<std::size_t>(lhs)] <
225  order[static_cast<std::size_t>(rhs)];
226 }

246 /*
247 Implementation of two C++17 constructs: conjunction, negation. This is needed
248 to avoid evaluating all the traits in a condition
249 
250 For example: not std::is_same<void, T>::value and has_value_type<T>::value
251 will not compile when T = void (on MSVC at least). Whereas
252 conjunction<negation<std::is_same<void, T>>, has_value_type<T>>::value will
253 stop evaluating if negation<...>::value == false
254 
255 Please note that those constructs must be used with caution, since symbols can
256 become very long quickly (which can slow down compilation and cause MSVC
257 internal compiler errors). Only use it when you have to (see example ahead).
258 */
259 template <class...>
260 struct conjunction : std::true_type {};
261 template <class B1>
262 struct conjunction<B1> : B1 {};
263 template <class B1, class... Bn>
264 struct conjunction<B1, Bn...>
265  : std::conditional<bool(B1::value), conjunction<Bn...>, B1>::type {};
266 
267 template <class B>
268 struct negation : std::integral_constant<bool, !B::value> {};

409 #define NLOHMANN_JSON_HAS_HELPER(type) \
410  template <typename T> \
411  struct has_##type { \
412  private: \
413  template <typename U, typename = typename U::type> \
414  static int detect(U&&); \
415  static void detect(...); \
416  \
417  public: \
418  static constexpr bool value = \
419  std::is_integral<decltype(detect(std::declval<T>()))>::value; \
420  }

429 template <bool B, class RealType, class CompatibleObjectType>
430 struct is_compatible_object_type_impl : std::false_type {};
431 
432 template <class RealType, class CompatibleObjectType>
433 struct is_compatible_object_type_impl<true, RealType, CompatibleObjectType> {
434  static constexpr auto value =
435  std::is_constructible<typename RealType::key_type,
436  typename CompatibleObjectType::key_type>::value and
437  std::is_constructible<typename RealType::mapped_type,
438  typename CompatibleObjectType::mapped_type>::value;
439 };

441 template <class BasicJsonType, class CompatibleObjectType>
442 struct is_compatible_object_type {
443  static auto constexpr value = is_compatible_object_type_impl<
444  conjunction<negation<std::is_same<void, CompatibleObjectType>>,
445  has_mapped_type<CompatibleObjectType>,
446  has_key_type<CompatibleObjectType>>::value,
447  typename BasicJsonType::object_t, CompatibleObjectType>::value;
448 };

450 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
451 struct is_basic_json_nested_type {
452  static auto constexpr value =
453  std::is_same<T, typename BasicJsonType::iterator>::value or
454  std::is_same<T, typename BasicJsonType::const_iterator>::value or
455  std::is_same<T, typename BasicJsonType::reverse_iterator>::value or
456  std::is_same<T, typename BasicJsonType::const_reverse_iterator>::value or
457  std::is_same<T, typename BasicJsonType::json_pointer>::value;
458 };

460 template <class BasicJsonType, class CompatibleArrayType>
461 struct is_compatible_array_type {
462  static auto constexpr value = conjunction<
463  negation<std::is_same<void, CompatibleArrayType>>,
464  negation<is_compatible_object_type<BasicJsonType, CompatibleArrayType>>,
465  negation<std::is_constructible<typename BasicJsonType::string_t,
466  CompatibleArrayType>>,
467  negation<is_basic_json_nested_type<BasicJsonType, CompatibleArrayType>>,
468  has_value_type<CompatibleArrayType>,
469  has_iterator<CompatibleArrayType>>::value;
470 };

623 // overloads for basic_json template parameters
624 template <
625  typename BasicJsonType, typename ArithmeticType,
626  enable_if_t<std::is_arithmetic<ArithmeticType>::value and
627  not std::is_same<ArithmeticType,
628  typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t>::value,
629  int> = 0>
630 void get_arithmetic_value(const BasicJsonType& j, ArithmeticType& val) {
631  switch (static_cast<value_t>(j)) {
632  case value_t::number_unsigned: {
633  val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(
634  *j.template get_ptr<
635  const typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t*>());
636  break;
637  }
638  case value_t::number_integer: {
639  val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(
640  *j.template get_ptr<
641  const typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t*>());
642  break;
643  }
644  case value_t::number_float: {
645  val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(
646  *j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t*>());
647  break;
648  }
649  default: {
650  JSON_THROW(
651  std::domain_error("type must be number, but is " + j.type_name()));
652  }
653  }
654 }

657 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t& b) {
658  if (not j.is_boolean()) {
659  JSON_THROW(

661  }
662  b = *j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t*>();
663 }

695  typename std::underlying_type<UnscopedEnumType>::type val;
696  get_arithmetic_value(j, val);
697  e = static_cast<UnscopedEnumType>(val);

703  JSON_THROW(

709 // forward_list doesn't have an insert method
710 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T, typename Allocator>
711 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, std::forward_list<T, Allocator>& l) {
712  // do not perform the check when user wants to retrieve jsons
713  // (except when it's null.. ?)
714  if (j.is_null()) {
715  JSON_THROW(
716  std::domain_error("type must be array, but is " + j.type_name()));
717  }
718  if (not std::is_same<T, BasicJsonType>::value) {
719  if (not j.is_array()) {
720  JSON_THROW(
721  std::domain_error("type must be array, but is " + j.type_name()));
722  }
723  }
724  for (auto it = j.rbegin(), end = j.rend(); it != end; ++it) {
725  l.push_front(it->template get<T>());
726  }
727 }

729 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleArrayType>
730 void from_json_array_impl(const BasicJsonType& j, CompatibleArrayType& arr,
731  priority_tag<0>) {
732  using std::begin;
733  using std::end;
734 
735  std::transform(
736  j.begin(), j.end(), std::inserter(arr, end(arr)),
737  [](const BasicJsonType& i) {
738  // get<BasicJsonType>() returns *this, this won't call a from_json
739  // method when value_type is BasicJsonType
740  return i.template get<typename CompatibleArrayType::value_type>();
741  });
742 }

744 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleArrayType>
745 auto from_json_array_impl(const BasicJsonType& j, CompatibleArrayType& arr,
746  priority_tag<1>)
747  -> decltype(
748  arr.reserve(std::declval<typename CompatibleArrayType::size_type>()),
749  void()) {
750  using std::begin;
751  using std::end;
752 
753  arr.reserve(j.size());
754  std::transform(
755  j.begin(), j.end(), std::inserter(arr, end(arr)),
756  [](const BasicJsonType& i) {
757  // get<BasicJsonType>() returns *this, this won't call a from_json
758  // method when value_type is BasicJsonType
759  return i.template get<typename CompatibleArrayType::value_type>();
760  });

763 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleArrayType,
764  enable_if_t<is_compatible_array_type<BasicJsonType,
765  CompatibleArrayType>::value and
766  not std::is_same<typename BasicJsonType::array_t,
767  CompatibleArrayType>::value,
768  int> = 0>
769 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, CompatibleArrayType& arr) {
770  if (j.is_null()) {
771  JSON_THROW(
772  std::domain_error("type must be array, but is " + j.type_name()));
773  }
774 
775  // when T == BasicJsonType, do not check if value_t is correct
776  if (not std::is_same<typename CompatibleArrayType::value_type,
777  BasicJsonType>::value) {
778  if (not j.is_array()) {
779  JSON_THROW(
780  std::domain_error("type must be array, but is " + j.type_name()));
781  }
782  }
783  from_json_array_impl(j, arr, priority_tag<1>{});
784 }

786 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleObjectType,
787  enable_if_t<is_compatible_object_type<BasicJsonType,
788  CompatibleObjectType>::value,
789  int> = 0>
790 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, CompatibleObjectType& obj) {
791  if (not j.is_object()) {
792  JSON_THROW(
793  std::domain_error("type must be object, but is " + j.type_name()));
794  }
795 
796  auto inner_object =
797  j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::object_t*>();
798  using std::begin;
799  using std::end;
800  // we could avoid the assignment, but this might require a for loop, which
801  // might be less efficient than the container constructor for some
802  // containers (would it?)
803  obj = CompatibleObjectType(begin(*inner_object), end(*inner_object));
804 }

806 // overload for arithmetic types, not chosen for basic_json template arguments
807 // (BooleanType, etc..); note: Is it really necessary to provide explicit
808 // overloads for boolean_t etc. in case of a custom BooleanType which is not
809 // an arithmetic type?
810 template <
811  typename BasicJsonType, typename ArithmeticType,
812  enable_if_t<
813  std::is_arithmetic<ArithmeticType>::value and
814  not std::is_same<ArithmeticType, typename BasicJsonType::
815  number_unsigned_t>::value and
816  not std::is_same<ArithmeticType, typename BasicJsonType::
817  number_integer_t>::value and
818  not std::is_same<ArithmeticType,
819  typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t>::value and
820  not std::is_same<ArithmeticType,
821  typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t>::value,
822  int> = 0>
823 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, ArithmeticType& val) {
824  switch (static_cast<value_t>(j)) {
825  case value_t::number_unsigned: {
826  val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(
827  *j.template get_ptr<
828  const typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t*>());
829  break;
830  }
831  case value_t::number_integer: {
832  val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(
833  *j.template get_ptr<
834  const typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t*>());
835  break;
836  }
837  case value_t::number_float: {
838  val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(
839  *j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t*>());
840  break;
841  }
842  case value_t::boolean: {
843  val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(
844  *j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t*>());
845  break;
846  }
847  default: {
848  JSON_THROW(
849  std::domain_error("type must be number, but is " + j.type_name()));
850  }
851  }
852 }

2077  basic_json(std::initializer_list<basic_json> init, bool type_deduction = true,
2078  value_t manual_type = value_t::array) {
2079  // check if each element is an array with two elements whose first
2080  // element is a string
2081  bool is_an_object =
2082  std::all_of(init.begin(), init.end(), [](const basic_json& element) {
2083  return element.is_array() and element.size() == 2 and
2084  element[0].is_string();
2085  });
2086 
2087  // adjust type if type deduction is not wanted
2088  if (not type_deduction) {
2089  // if array is wanted, do not create an object though possible
2090  if (manual_type == value_t::array) {
2091  is_an_object = false;
2092  }
2093 
2094  // if object is wanted but impossible, throw an exception
2095  if (manual_type == value_t::object and not is_an_object) {
2096  JSON_THROW(
2097  std::domain_error("cannot create object from initializer list"));
2098  }
2099  }
2100 
2101  if (is_an_object) {
2102  // the initializer list is a list of pairs -> create object
2103  m_type = value_t::object;
2104  m_value = value_t::object;
2105 
2106  std::for_each(
2107  init.begin(), init.end(), [this](const basic_json& element) {
2108  m_value.object->emplace(*(element[0].m_value.string), element[1]);
2109  });
2110  } else {
2111  // the initializer list describes an array -> create array
2112  m_type = value_t::array;
2113  m_value.array = create<array_t>(init);
2114  }
2115 
2116  assert_invariant();
2117  }

2257  template <class InputIT,
2258  typename std::enable_if<
2259  std::is_same<InputIT, typename basic_json_t::iterator>::value or
2260  std::is_same<InputIT,
2261  typename basic_json_t::const_iterator>::value,
2262  int>::type = 0>
2263  basic_json(InputIT first, InputIT last) {
2264  assert(first.m_object != nullptr);
2265  assert(last.m_object != nullptr);
2266 
2267  // make sure iterator fits the current value
2268  if (first.m_object != last.m_object) {
2269  JSON_THROW(std::domain_error("iterators are not compatible"));
2270  }
2271 
2272  // copy type from first iterator
2273  m_type = first.m_object->m_type;
2274 
2275  // check if iterator range is complete for primitive values
2276  switch (m_type) {
2277  case value_t::boolean:
2278  case value_t::number_float:
2279  case value_t::number_integer:
2280  case value_t::number_unsigned:
2281  case value_t::string: {
2282  if (not first.m_it.primitive_iterator.is_begin() or
2283  not last.m_it.primitive_iterator.is_end()) {
2284  JSON_THROW(std::out_of_range("iterators out of range"));
2285  }
2286  break;
2287  }
2288 
2289  default: { break; }
2290  }
2291 
2292  switch (m_type) {
2293  case value_t::number_integer: {
2294  m_value.number_integer = first.m_object->m_value.number_integer;
2295  break;
2296  }
2297 
2298  case value_t::number_unsigned: {
2299  m_value.number_unsigned = first.m_object->m_value.number_unsigned;
2300  break;
2301  }
2302 
2303  case value_t::number_float: {
2304  m_value.number_float = first.m_object->m_value.number_float;
2305  break;
2306  }
2307 
2308  case value_t::boolean: {
2309  m_value.boolean = first.m_object->m_value.boolean;
2310  break;
2311  }
2312 
2313  case value_t::string: {
2314  m_value = *first.m_object->m_value.string;
2315  break;
2316  }
2317 
2318  case value_t::object: {
2319  m_value.object = create<object_t>(first.m_it.object_iterator,
2320  last.m_it.object_iterator);
2321  break;
2322  }

5744  return (basic_json(lhs) != rhs);
5745  }

5771  friend bool operator<(const_reference lhs, const_reference rhs) noexcept {
5772  const auto lhs_type = lhs.type();
5773  const auto rhs_type = rhs.type();
5774 
5775  if (lhs_type == rhs_type) {
5776  switch (lhs_type) {
5777  case value_t::array: {
5778  return *lhs.m_value.array < *rhs.m_value.array;
5779  }
5780  case value_t::object: {
5781  return *lhs.m_value.object < *rhs.m_value.object;
5782  }
5783  case value_t::null: {
5784  return false;
5785  }
5786  case value_t::string: {
5787  return *lhs.m_value.string < *rhs.m_value.string;
5788  }
5789  case value_t::boolean: {
5790  return lhs.m_value.boolean < rhs.m_value.boolean;
5791  }
5792  case value_t::number_integer: {
5793  return lhs.m_value.number_integer < rhs.m_value.number_integer;
5794  }
5795  case value_t::number_unsigned: {
5796  return lhs.m_value.number_unsigned < rhs.m_value.number_unsigned;
5797  }
5798  case value_t::number_float: {
5799  return lhs.m_value.number_float < rhs.m_value.number_float;
5800  }
5801  default: { return false; }
5802  }
5803  } else if (lhs_type == value_t::number_integer and
5804  rhs_type == value_t::number_float) {
5805  return static_cast<number_float_t>(lhs.m_value.number_integer) <
5806  rhs.m_value.number_float;
5807  } else if (lhs_type == value_t::number_float and
5808  rhs_type == value_t::number_integer) {
5809  return lhs.m_value.number_float <
5810  static_cast<number_float_t>(rhs.m_value.number_integer);
5811  } else if (lhs_type == value_t::number_unsigned and
5812  rhs_type == value_t::number_float) {
5813  return static_cast<number_float_t>(lhs.m_value.number_unsigned) <
5814  rhs.m_value.number_float;
5815  } else if (lhs_type == value_t::number_float and
5816  rhs_type == value_t::number_unsigned) {
5817  return lhs.m_value.number_float <
5818  static_cast<number_float_t>(rhs.m_value.number_unsigned);
5819  } else if (lhs_type == value_t::number_integer and
5820  rhs_type == value_t::number_unsigned) {
5821  return lhs.m_value.number_integer <
5822  static_cast<number_integer_t>(rhs.m_value.number_unsigned);
5823  } else if (lhs_type == value_t::number_unsigned and
5824  rhs_type == value_t::number_integer) {
5825  return static_cast<number_integer_t>(lhs.m_value.number_unsigned) <
5826  rhs.m_value.number_integer;
5827  }
5828 
5829  // We only reach this line if we cannot compare values. In that case,
5830  // we compare types. Note we have to call the operator explicitly,
5831  // because MSVC has problems otherwise.
5832  return operator<(lhs_type, rhs_type);
5833  }

6109  template <class IteratorType,
6110  typename std::enable_if<
6111  std::is_base_of<std::random_access_iterator_tag,
6112  typename std::iterator_traits<
6113  IteratorType>::iterator_category>::value,
6114  int>::type = 0>
6115  static basic_json parse(IteratorType first, IteratorType last,
6116  const parser_callback_t cb = nullptr) {
6117  // assertion to check that the iterator range is indeed contiguous,
6118  // see http://stackoverflow.com/a/35008842/266378 for more discussion
6119  assert(std::accumulate(
6120  first, last, std::pair<bool, int>(true, 0),
6121  [&first](std::pair<bool, int> res, decltype(*first) val) {
6122  res.first &= (val == *(std::next(std::addressof(*first),
6123  res.second++)));
6124  return res;
6125  })
6126  .first);
6127 
6128  // assertion to check that each element is 1 byte long
6129  static_assert(
6130  sizeof(typename std::iterator_traits<IteratorType>::value_type) == 1,
6131  "each element in the iterator range must have the size of 1 byte");
6132 
6133  // if iterator range is empty, create a parser with an empty string
6134  // to generate "unexpected EOF" error message
6135  if (std::distance(first, last) <= 0) {
6136  return parser("").parse();
6137  }
6138 
6139  return parser(first, last, cb).parse();
6140  }

6249  template <typename T>
6250  static void add_to_vector(std::vector<uint8_t>& vec, size_t bytes,
6251  const T number) {
6252  assert(bytes == 1 or bytes == 2 or bytes == 4 or bytes == 8);
6253 
6254  switch (bytes) {
6255  case 8: {
6256  vec.push_back(static_cast<uint8_t>(
6257  (static_cast<uint64_t>(number) >> 070) & 0xff));
6258  vec.push_back(static_cast<uint8_t>(
6259  (static_cast<uint64_t>(number) >> 060) & 0xff));
6260  vec.push_back(static_cast<uint8_t>(
6261  (static_cast<uint64_t>(number) >> 050) & 0xff));
6262  vec.push_back(static_cast<uint8_t>(
6263  (static_cast<uint64_t>(number) >> 040) & 0xff));
6264  vec.push_back(static_cast<uint8_t>((number >> 030) & 0xff));
6265  vec.push_back(static_cast<uint8_t>((number >> 020) & 0xff));
6266  vec.push_back(static_cast<uint8_t>((number >> 010) & 0xff));
6267  vec.push_back(static_cast<uint8_t>(number & 0xff));
6268  break;
6269  }
6270 
6271  case 4: {
6272  vec.push_back(static_cast<uint8_t>((number >> 030) & 0xff));
6273  vec.push_back(static_cast<uint8_t>((number >> 020) & 0xff));
6274  vec.push_back(static_cast<uint8_t>((number >> 010) & 0xff));
6275  vec.push_back(static_cast<uint8_t>(number & 0xff));
6276  break;
6277  }
6278 
6279  case 2: {
6280  vec.push_back(static_cast<uint8_t>((number >> 010) & 0xff));
6281  vec.push_back(static_cast<uint8_t>(number & 0xff));
6282  break;
6283  }
6284 
6285  case 1: {
6286  vec.push_back(static_cast<uint8_t>(number & 0xff));
6287  break;
6288  }
6289  }
6290  }

6328  template <typename T>
6329  static T get_from_vector(const std::vector<uint8_t>& vec,
6330  const size_t current_index) {
6331  if (current_index + sizeof(T) + 1 > vec.size()) {
6332  JSON_THROW(std::out_of_range("cannot read " +
6333  nlohmann::std_support::to_string(sizeof(T)) +
6334  " bytes from vector"));
6335  }
6336 
6337  T result;
6338  auto* ptr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(&result);
6339  for (size_t i = 0; i < sizeof(T); ++i) {
6340  *ptr++ = vec[current_index + sizeof(T) - i];
6341  }
6342  return result;
6343  }

6355  static void to_msgpack_internal(const basic_json& j,
6356  std::vector<uint8_t>& v) {
6357  switch (j.type()) {
6358  case value_t::null: {
6359  // nil
6360  v.push_back(0xc0);
6361  break;
6362  }
6363 
6364  case value_t::boolean: {
6365  // true and false
6366  v.push_back(j.m_value.boolean ? 0xc3 : 0xc2);
6367  break;
6368  }
6369 
6370  case value_t::number_integer: {
6371  if (j.m_value.number_integer >= 0) {
6372  // MessagePack does not differentiate between positive
6373  // signed integers and unsigned integers. Therefore, we
6374  // used the code from the value_t::number_unsigned case
6375  // here.
6376  if (j.m_value.number_unsigned < 128) {
6377  // positive fixnum
6378  add_to_vector(v, 1, j.m_value.number_unsigned);
6379  } else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <=
6380  std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::max()) {
6381  // uint 8
6382  v.push_back(0xcc);
6383  add_to_vector(v, 1, j.m_value.number_unsigned);
6384  } else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <=
6385  std::numeric_limits<uint16_t>::max()) {
6386  // uint 16
6387  v.push_back(0xcd);
6388  add_to_vector(v, 2, j.m_value.number_unsigned);
6389  } else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <=
6390  std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max()) {
6391  // uint 32
6392  v.push_back(0xce);
6393  add_to_vector(v, 4, j.m_value.number_unsigned);
6394  } else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <=
6395  std::numeric_limits<uint64_t>::max()) {
6396  // uint 64
6397  v.push_back(0xcf);
6398  add_to_vector(v, 8, j.m_value.number_unsigned);
6399  }
6400  } else {
6401  if (j.m_value.number_integer >= -32) {
6402  // negative fixnum
6403  add_to_vector(v, 1, j.m_value.number_integer);
6404  } else if (j.m_value.number_integer >=
6405  std::numeric_limits<int8_t>::min() and
6406  j.m_value.number_integer <=
6407  std::numeric_limits<int8_t>::max()) {
6408  // int 8
6409  v.push_back(0xd0);
6410  add_to_vector(v, 1, j.m_value.number_integer);
6411  } else if (j.m_value.number_integer >=
6412  std::numeric_limits<int16_t>::min() and
6413  j.m_value.number_integer <=
6414  std::numeric_limits<int16_t>::max()) {
6415  // int 16
6416  v.push_back(0xd1);
6417  add_to_vector(v, 2, j.m_value.number_integer);
6418  } else if (j.m_value.number_integer >=
6419  std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min() and
6420  j.m_value.number_integer <=
6421  std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::max()) {
6422  // int 32
6423  v.push_back(0xd2);
6424  add_to_vector(v, 4, j.m_value.number_integer);
6425  } else if (j.m_value.number_integer >=
6426  std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::min() and
6427  j.m_value.number_integer <=
6428  std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::max()) {
6429  // int 64
6430  v.push_back(0xd3);
6431  add_to_vector(v, 8, j.m_value.number_integer);
6432  }
6433  }
6434  break;
6435  }
6436 
6437  case value_t::number_unsigned: {
6438  if (j.m_value.number_unsigned < 128) {
6439  // positive fixnum
6440  add_to_vector(v, 1, j.m_value.number_unsigned);
6441  } else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <=
6442  std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::max()) {
6443  // uint 8
6444  v.push_back(0xcc);
6445  add_to_vector(v, 1, j.m_value.number_unsigned);
6446  } else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <=
6447  std::numeric_limits<uint16_t>::max()) {
6448  // uint 16
6449  v.push_back(0xcd);
6450  add_to_vector(v, 2, j.m_value.number_unsigned);
6451  } else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <=
6452  std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max()) {
6453  // uint 32
6454  v.push_back(0xce);
6455  add_to_vector(v, 4, j.m_value.number_unsigned);
6456  } else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <=
6457  std::numeric_limits<uint64_t>::max()) {
6458  // uint 64
6459  v.push_back(0xcf);
6460  add_to_vector(v, 8, j.m_value.number_unsigned);
6461  }
6462  break;
6463  }
6464 
6465  case value_t::number_float: {
6466  // float 64
6467  v.push_back(0xcb);
6468  const auto* helper =
6469  reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(&(j.m_value.number_float));
6470  for (size_t i = 0; i < 8; ++i) {
6471  v.push_back(helper[7 - i]);
6472  }
6473  break;
6474  }
6475 
6476  case value_t::string: {
6477  const auto N = j.m_value.string->size();
6478  if (N <= 31) {
6479  // fixstr
6480  v.push_back(static_cast<uint8_t>(0xa0 | N));
6481  } else if (N <= 255) {
6482  // str 8
6483  v.push_back(0xd9);
6484  add_to_vector(v, 1, N);
6485  } else if (N <= 65535) {
6486  // str 16
6487  v.push_back(0xda);
6488  add_to_vector(v, 2, N);
6489  } else if (N <= 4294967295) {
6490  // str 32
6491  v.push_back(0xdb);
6492  add_to_vector(v, 4, N);
6493  }
6494 
6495  // append string
6496  std::copy(j.m_value.string->begin(), j.m_value.string->end(),
6497  std::back_inserter(v));
6498  break;
6499  }
6500 
6501  case value_t::array: {
6502  const auto N = j.m_value.array->size();
6503  if (N <= 15) {
6504  // fixarray
6505  v.push_back(static_cast<uint8_t>(0x90 | N));
6506  } else if (N <= 0xffff) {
6507  // array 16
6508  v.push_back(0xdc);
6509  add_to_vector(v, 2, N);
6510  } else if (N <= 0xffffffff) {
6511  // array 32
6512  v.push_back(0xdd);
6513  add_to_vector(v, 4, N);
6514  }
6515 
6516  // append each element
6517  for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.array) {
6518  to_msgpack_internal(el, v);
6519  }
6520  break;
6521  }
6522 
6523  case value_t::object: {
6524  const auto N = j.m_value.object->size();
6525  if (N <= 15) {
6526  // fixmap
6527  v.push_back(static_cast<uint8_t>(0x80 | (N & 0xf)));
6528  } else if (N <= 65535) {
6529  // map 16
6530  v.push_back(0xde);
6531  add_to_vector(v, 2, N);
6532  } else if (N <= 4294967295) {
6533  // map 32
6534  v.push_back(0xdf);
6535  add_to_vector(v, 4, N);
6536  }
6537 
6538  // append each element
6539  for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.object) {
6540  to_msgpack_internal(el.first, v);
6541  to_msgpack_internal(el.second, v);
6542  }
6543  break;
6544  }
6545 
6546  default: { break; }
6547  }
6548  }

6560  static void to_cbor_internal(const basic_json& j, std::vector<uint8_t>& v) {
6561  switch (j.type()) {
6562  case value_t::null: {
6563  v.push_back(0xf6);
6564  break;
6565  }
6566 
6567  case value_t::boolean: {
6568  v.push_back(j.m_value.boolean ? 0xf5 : 0xf4);
6569  break;
6570  }
6571 
6572  case value_t::number_integer: {
6573  if (j.m_value.number_integer >= 0) {
6574  // CBOR does not differentiate between positive signed
6575  // integers and unsigned integers. Therefore, we used the
6576  // code from the value_t::number_unsigned case here.
6577  if (j.m_value.number_integer <= 0x17) {
6578  add_to_vector(v, 1, j.m_value.number_integer);
6579  } else if (j.m_value.number_integer <=
6580  std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::max()) {
6581  v.push_back(0x18);
6582  // one-byte uint8_t
6583  add_to_vector(v, 1, j.m_value.number_integer);
6584  } else if (j.m_value.number_integer <=
6585  std::numeric_limits<uint16_t>::max()) {
6586  v.push_back(0x19);
6587  // two-byte uint16_t
6588  add_to_vector(v, 2, j.m_value.number_integer);
6589  } else if (j.m_value.number_integer <=
6590  std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max()) {
6591  v.push_back(0x1a);
6592  // four-byte uint32_t
6593  add_to_vector(v, 4, j.m_value.number_integer);
6594  } else {
6595  v.push_back(0x1b);
6596  // eight-byte uint64_t
6597  add_to_vector(v, 8, j.m_value.number_integer);
6598  }
6599  } else {
6600  // The conversions below encode the sign in the first
6601  // byte, and the value is converted to a positive number.
6602  const auto positive_number = -1 - j.m_value.number_integer;
6603  if (j.m_value.number_integer >= -24) {
6604  v.push_back(static_cast<uint8_t>(0x20 + positive_number));
6605  } else if (positive_number <= std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::max()) {
6606  // int 8
6607  v.push_back(0x38);
6608  add_to_vector(v, 1, positive_number);
6609  } else if (positive_number <= std::numeric_limits<uint16_t>::max()) {
6610  // int 16
6611  v.push_back(0x39);
6612  add_to_vector(v, 2, positive_number);
6613  } else if (positive_number <= std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max()) {
6614  // int 32
6615  v.push_back(0x3a);
6616  add_to_vector(v, 4, positive_number);
6617  } else {
6618  // int 64
6619  v.push_back(0x3b);
6620  add_to_vector(v, 8, positive_number);
6621  }
6622  }
6623  break;
6624  }
6625 
6626  case value_t::number_unsigned: {
6627  if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= 0x17) {
6628  v.push_back(static_cast<uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_unsigned));
6629  } else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= 0xff) {
6630  v.push_back(0x18);
6631  // one-byte uint8_t
6632  add_to_vector(v, 1, j.m_value.number_unsigned);
6633  } else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= 0xffff) {
6634  v.push_back(0x19);
6635  // two-byte uint16_t
6636  add_to_vector(v, 2, j.m_value.number_unsigned);
6637  } else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= 0xffffffff) {
6638  v.push_back(0x1a);
6639  // four-byte uint32_t
6640  add_to_vector(v, 4, j.m_value.number_unsigned);
6641  } else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= 0xffffffffffffffff) {
6642  v.push_back(0x1b);
6643  // eight-byte uint64_t
6644  add_to_vector(v, 8, j.m_value.number_unsigned);
6645  }
6646  break;
6647  }
6648 
6649  case value_t::number_float: {
6650  // Double-Precision Float
6651  v.push_back(0xfb);
6652  const auto* helper =
6653  reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(&(j.m_value.number_float));
6654  for (size_t i = 0; i < 8; ++i) {
6655  v.push_back(helper[7 - i]);
6656  }
6657  break;
6658  }
6659 
6660  case value_t::string: {
6661  const auto N = j.m_value.string->size();
6662  if (N <= 0x17) {
6663  v.push_back(0x60 +
6664  static_cast<uint8_t>(N)); // 1 byte for string + size
6665  } else if (N <= 0xff) {
6666  v.push_back(0x78); // one-byte uint8_t for N
6667  add_to_vector(v, 1, N);
6668  } else if (N <= 0xffff) {
6669  v.push_back(0x79); // two-byte uint16_t for N
6670  add_to_vector(v, 2, N);
6671  } else if (N <= 0xffffffff) {
6672  v.push_back(0x7a); // four-byte uint32_t for N
6673  add_to_vector(v, 4, N);
6674  }
6675  // LCOV_EXCL_START
6676  else if (N <= 0xffffffffffffffff) {
6677  v.push_back(0x7b); // eight-byte uint64_t for N
6678  add_to_vector(v, 8, N);
6679  }
6680  // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
6681 
6682  // append string
6683  std::copy(j.m_value.string->begin(), j.m_value.string->end(),
6684  std::back_inserter(v));
6685  break;
6686  }
6687 
6688  case value_t::array: {
6689  const auto N = j.m_value.array->size();
6690  if (N <= 0x17) {
6691  v.push_back(0x80 +
6692  static_cast<uint8_t>(N)); // 1 byte for array + size
6693  } else if (N <= 0xff) {
6694  v.push_back(0x98); // one-byte uint8_t for N
6695  add_to_vector(v, 1, N);
6696  } else if (N <= 0xffff) {
6697  v.push_back(0x99); // two-byte uint16_t for N
6698  add_to_vector(v, 2, N);
6699  } else if (N <= 0xffffffff) {
6700  v.push_back(0x9a); // four-byte uint32_t for N
6701  add_to_vector(v, 4, N);
6702  }
6703  // LCOV_EXCL_START
6704  else if (N <= 0xffffffffffffffff) {
6705  v.push_back(0x9b); // eight-byte uint64_t for N
6706  add_to_vector(v, 8, N);
6707  }
6708  // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
6709 
6710  // append each element
6711  for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.array) {
6712  to_cbor_internal(el, v);
6713  }
6714  break;
6715  }
6716 
6717  case value_t::object: {
6718  const auto N = j.m_value.object->size();
6719  if (N <= 0x17) {
6720  v.push_back(0xa0 +
6721  static_cast<uint8_t>(N)); // 1 byte for object + size
6722  } else if (N <= 0xff) {
6723  v.push_back(0xb8);
6724  add_to_vector(v, 1, N); // one-byte uint8_t for N
6725  } else if (N <= 0xffff) {
6726  v.push_back(0xb9);
6727  add_to_vector(v, 2, N); // two-byte uint16_t for N
6728  } else if (N <= 0xffffffff) {
6729  v.push_back(0xba);
6730  add_to_vector(v, 4, N); // four-byte uint32_t for N
6731  }
6732  // LCOV_EXCL_START
6733  else if (N <= 0xffffffffffffffff) {
6734  v.push_back(0xbb);
6735  add_to_vector(v, 8, N); // eight-byte uint64_t for N
6736  }
6737  // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
6738 
6739  // append each element
6740  for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.object) {
6741  to_cbor_internal(el.first, v);
6742  to_cbor_internal(el.second, v);
6743  }
6744  break;
6745  }
6746 
6747  default: { break; }
6748  }
6749  }

6751  /*
6752  @brief checks if given lengths do not exceed the size of a given vector
6753 
6754  To secure the access to the byte vector during CBOR/MessagePack
6755  deserialization, bytes are copied from the vector into buffers. This
6756  function checks if the number of bytes to copy (@a len) does not exceed
6757  the size @s size of the vector. Additionally, an @a offset is given from
6758  where to start reading the bytes.
6759 
6760  This function checks whether reading the bytes is safe; that is, offset is
6761  a valid index in the vector, offset+len
6762 
6763  @param[in] size size of the byte vector
6764  @param[in] len number of bytes to read
6765  @param[in] offset offset where to start reading
6766 
6767  vec: x x x x x X X X X X
6768  ^ ^ ^
6769  0 offset len
6770 
6771  @throws out_of_range if `len > v.size()`
6772  */
6773  static void check_length(const size_t size, const size_t len,
6774  const size_t offset) {
6775  // simple case: requested length is greater than the vector's length
6776  if (len > size or offset > size) {
6777  JSON_THROW(std::out_of_range("len out of range"));
6778  }
6779 
6780  // second case: adding offset would result in overflow
6781  if ((size > (std::numeric_limits<size_t>::max() - offset))) {
6782  JSON_THROW(std::out_of_range("len+offset out of range"));
6783  }
6784 
6785  // last case: reading past the end of the vector
6786  if (len + offset > size) {
6787  JSON_THROW(std::out_of_range("len+offset out of range"));
6788  }
6789  }

6805  static basic_json from_msgpack_internal(const std::vector<uint8_t>& v,
6806  size_t& idx) {
6807  // make sure reading 1 byte is safe
6808  check_length(v.size(), 1, idx);
6809 
6810  // store and increment index
6811  const size_t current_idx = idx++;
6812 
6813  if (v[current_idx] <= 0xbf) {
6814  if (v[current_idx] <= 0x7f) // positive fixint
6815  {
6816  return v[current_idx];
6817  }
6818  if (v[current_idx] <= 0x8f) // fixmap
6819  {
6820  basic_json result = value_t::object;
6821  const size_t len = v[current_idx] & 0x0f;
6822  for (size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i) {
6823  std::string key = from_msgpack_internal(v, idx);
6824  result[key] = from_msgpack_internal(v, idx);
6825  }
6826  return result;
6827  } else if (v[current_idx] <= 0x9f) // fixarray
6828  {
6829  basic_json result = value_t::array;
6830  const size_t len = v[current_idx] & 0x0f;
6831  for (size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i) {
6832  result.push_back(from_msgpack_internal(v, idx));
6833  }
6834  return result;
6835  } else // fixstr
6836  {
6837  const size_t len = v[current_idx] & 0x1f;
6838  const size_t offset = current_idx + 1;
6839  idx += len; // skip content bytes
6840  check_length(v.size(), len, offset);
6841  return std::string(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(v.data()) + offset,
6842  len);
6843  }
6844  } else if (v[current_idx] >= 0xe0) // negative fixint
6845  {
6846  return static_cast<int8_t>(v[current_idx]);

6852  }
6853

6855  {

6870  v.at(current_idx + 1 + byte);
6871  }

6873  return res;

6880  for (size_t byte = 0; byte < sizeof(double); ++byte) {
6881  reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(&res)[sizeof(double) - byte - 1] =
6882  v.at(current_idx + 1 + byte);
6883  }
6884  idx += sizeof(double); // skip content bytes
6885  return res;
6886  }

7334  result.push_back(from_cbor_internal(v, idx));
7335  }
7336  // skip break byte (0xFF)
7337  idx += 1;
7338  return result;
7339  }
7340 
7341  // map (0x00..0x17 pairs of data items follow)
7342  case 0xa0:
7343  case 0xa1:
7344  case 0xa2:
7345  case 0xa3:
7346  case 0xa4:
7347  case 0xa5:
7348  case 0xa6:
7349  case 0xa7:
7350  case 0xa8:
7351  case 0xa9:
7352  case 0xaa:
7353  case 0xab:
7354  case 0xac:
7355  case 0xad:
7356  case 0xae:
7357  case 0xaf:
7358  case 0xb0:
7359  case 0xb1:
7360  case 0xb2:
7361  case 0xb3:
7362  case 0xb4:
7363  case 0xb5:
7364  case 0xb6:
7365  case 0xb7: {
7366  basic_json result = value_t::object;
7367  const auto len = static_cast<size_t>(v[current_idx] - 0xa0);
7368  for (size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i) {
7369  std::string key = from_cbor_internal(v, idx);
7370  result[key] = from_cbor_internal(v, idx);
7371  }
7372  return result;
7373  }
7374 
7375  case 0xb8: // map (one-byte uint8_t for n follows)
7376  {
7377  basic_json result = value_t::object;
7378  const auto len =
7379  static_cast<size_t>(get_from_vector<uint8_t>(v, current_idx));
7380  idx += 1; // skip 1 size byte
7381  for (size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i) {
7382  std::string key = from_cbor_internal(v, idx);
7383  result[key] = from_cbor_internal(v, idx);
7384  }
7385  return result;
7386  }
7387 
7388  case 0xb9: // map (two-byte uint16_t for n follow)
7389  {
7390  basic_json result = value_t::object;
7391  const auto len =
7392  static_cast<size_t>(get_from_vector<uint16_t>(v, current_idx));
7393  idx += 2; // skip 2 size bytes
7394  for (size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i) {
7395  std::string key = from_cbor_internal(v, idx);
7396  result[key] = from_cbor_internal(v, idx);
7397  }
7398  return result;
7399  }
7400 
7401  case 0xba: // map (four-byte uint32_t for n follow)
7402  {
7403  basic_json result = value_t::object;
7404  const auto len =
7405  static_cast<size_t>(get_from_vector<uint32_t>(v, current_idx));
7406  idx += 4; // skip 4 size bytes
7407  for (size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i) {
7408  std::string key = from_cbor_internal(v, idx);
7409  result[key] = from_cbor_internal(v, idx);
7410  }
7411  return result;
7412  }
7413 
7414  case 0xbb: // map (eight-byte uint64_t for n follow)
7415  {
7416  basic_json result = value_t::object;
7417  const auto len =
7418  static_cast<size_t>(get_from_vector<uint64_t>(v, current_idx));
7419  idx += 8; // skip 8 size bytes
7420  for (size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i) {
7421  std::string key = from_cbor_internal(v, idx);
7422  result[key] = from_cbor_internal(v, idx);
7423  }
7424  return result;
7425  }
7426 
7427  case 0xbf: // map (indefinite length)
7428  {
7429  basic_json result = value_t::object;
7430  while (v.at(idx) != 0xff) {
7431  std::string key = from_cbor_internal(v, idx);
7432  result[key] = from_cbor_internal(v, idx);
7433  }
7434  // skip break byte (0xFF)
7435  idx += 1;
7436  return result;
7437  }
7438 
7439  case 0xf4: // false
7440  {
7441  return false;
7442  }
7443 
7444  case 0xf5: // true
7445  {
7446  return true;
7447  }
7448 
7449  case 0xf6: // null
7450  {
7451  return value_t::null;
7452  }
7453 
7454  case 0xf9: // Half-Precision Float (two-byte IEEE 754)
7455  {
7456  idx += 2; // skip two content bytes
7457 
7458  // code from RFC 7049, Appendix D, Figure 3:
7459  // As half-precision floating-point numbers were only added to
7460  // IEEE 754 in 2008, today's programming platforms often still
7461  // only have limited support for them. It is very easy to
7462  // include at least decoding support for them even without such
7463  // support. An example of a small decoder for half-precision
7464  // floating-point numbers in the C language is shown in Fig. 3.
7465  const int half = (v.at(current_idx + 1) << 8) + v.at(current_idx + 2);
7466  const int exp = (half >> 10) & 0x1f;
7467  const int mant = half & 0x3ff;
7468  double val;
7469  if (exp == 0) {
7470  val = std::ldexp(mant, -24);
7471  } else if (exp != 31) {
7472  val = std::ldexp(mant + 1024, exp - 25);
7473  } else {
7474  val = mant == 0 ? std::numeric_limits<double>::infinity()
7475  : std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN();
7476  }
7477  return (half & 0x8000) != 0 ? -val : val;
7478  }
7479 
7480  case 0xfa: // Single-Precision Float (four-byte IEEE 754)
7481  {
7482  // copy bytes in reverse order into the float variable
7483  float res;
7484  for (size_t byte = 0; byte < sizeof(float); ++byte) {
7485  reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(&res)[sizeof(float) - byte - 1] =
7486  v.at(current_idx + 1 + byte);
7487  }
7488  idx += sizeof(float); // skip content bytes
7489  return res;
7490  }
7491 
7492  case 0xfb: // Double-Precision Float (eight-byte IEEE 754)
7493  {
7494  // copy bytes in reverse order into the double variable
7495  double res;
7496  for (size_t byte = 0; byte < sizeof(double); ++byte) {
7497  reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(&res)[sizeof(double) - byte - 1] =
7498  v.at(current_idx + 1 + byte);
7499  }
7500  idx += sizeof(double); // skip content bytes
7501  return res;
7502  }
7503 
7504  default: // anything else (0xFF is handled inside the other types)
7505  {
7506  JSON_THROW(std::invalid_argument(
7507  "error parsing a CBOR @ " +
7508  nlohmann::std_support::to_string(current_idx) + ": " +
7509  nlohmann::std_support::to_string(
7510  static_cast<int>(v[current_idx]))));
7511  }
7512  }
7513  }

7679  private:
7688  static std::size_t extra_space(const string_t& s) noexcept {
7689  return std::accumulate(s.begin(), s.end(), size_t{},
7690  [](size_t res, typename string_t::value_type c) {
7691  switch (c) {
7692  case '"':
7693  case '\\':
7694  case '\b':
7695  case '\f':
7696  case '\n':
7697  case '\r':
7698  case '\t': {
7699  // from c (1 byte) to \x (2 bytes)
7700  return res + 1;
7701  }
7702 
7703  default: {
7704  if (c >= 0x00 and c <= 0x1f) {
7705  // from c (1 byte) to \uxxxx (6 bytes)
7706  return res + 5;
7707  }
7708 
7709  return res;
7710  }
7711  }
7712  });
7713  }

7728  static string_t escape_string(const string_t& s) {
7729  const auto space = extra_space(s);
7730  if (space == 0) {
7731  return s;
7732  }
7733 
7734  // create a result string of necessary size
7735  string_t result(s.size() + space, '\\');
7736  std::size_t pos = 0;
7737 
7738  for (const auto& c : s) {
7739  switch (c) {
7740  // quotation mark (0x22)
7741  case '"': {
7742  result[pos + 1] = '"';
7743  pos += 2;
7744  break;
7745  }
7746 
7747  // reverse solidus (0x5c)
7748  case '\\': {
7749  // nothing to change
7750  pos += 2;
7751  break;
7752  }
7753 
7754  // backspace (0x08)
7755  case '\b': {
7756  result[pos + 1] = 'b';
7757  pos += 2;
7758  break;
7759  }
7760 
7761  // formfeed (0x0c)
7762  case '\f': {
7763  result[pos + 1] = 'f';
7764  pos += 2;
7765  break;
7766  }
7767 
7768  // newline (0x0a)
7769  case '\n': {
7770  result[pos + 1] = 'n';
7771  pos += 2;
7772  break;
7773  }
7774 
7775  // carriage return (0x0d)
7776  case '\r': {
7777  result[pos + 1] = 'r';
7778  pos += 2;
7779  break;
7780  }
7781 
7782  // horizontal tab (0x09)
7783  case '\t': {
7784  result[pos + 1] = 't';
7785  pos += 2;
7786  break;
7787  }
7788 
7789  default: {
7790  if (c >= 0x00 and c <= 0x1f) {
7791  // convert a number 0..15 to its hex representation
7792  // (0..f)
7793  static const char hexify[16] = {'0', '1', '2', '3', '4', '5',
7794  '6', '7', '8', '9', 'a', 'b',
7795  'c', 'd', 'e', 'f'};
7796 
7797  // print character c as \uxxxx
7798  for (const char m :
7799  {'u', '0', '0', hexify[c >> 4], hexify[c & 0x0f]}) {
7800  result[++pos] = m;
7801  }
7802 
7803  ++pos;
7804  } else {
7805  // all other characters are added as-is
7806  result[pos++] = c;
7807  }
7808  break;
7809  }
7810  }
7811  }
7812 
7813  return result;
7814  }

7819  struct numtostr {
7820  public:
7821  template <typename NumberType>
7822  numtostr(NumberType value) {
7823  x_write(value, std::is_integral<NumberType>());
7824  }
7825 
7826  const char* c_str() const { return m_buf.data(); }
7827 
7828  private:
7830  std::array<char, 64> m_buf{{}};
7831 
7832  template <typename NumberType>
7833  void x_write(NumberType x, /*is_integral=*/std::true_type) {
7834  // special case for "0"
7835  if (x == 0) {
7836  m_buf[0] = '0';
7837  return;
7838  }
7839 
7840  const bool is_negative = x < 0;
7841  size_t i = 0;
7842 
7843  // spare 1 byte for '\0'
7844  while (x != 0 and i < m_buf.size() - 1) {
7845  const auto digit = std::labs(static_cast<long>(x % 10));
7846  m_buf[i++] = static_cast<char>('0' + digit);
7847  x /= 10;
7848  }
7849 
7850  // make sure the number has been processed completely
7851  assert(x == 0);
7852 
7853  if (is_negative) {
7854  // make sure there is capacity for the '-'
7855  assert(i < m_buf.size() - 2);
7856  m_buf[i++] = '-';
7857  }
7858 
7859  std::reverse(m_buf.begin(), m_buf.begin() + i);
7860  }
7861 
7862  template <typename NumberType>
7863  void x_write(NumberType x, /*is_integral=*/std::false_type) {
7864  // special case for 0.0 and -0.0
7865  if (x == 0) {
7866  size_t i = 0;
7867  if (std::signbit(x)) {
7868  m_buf[i++] = '-';
7869  }
7870  m_buf[i++] = '0';
7871  m_buf[i++] = '.';
7872  m_buf[i] = '0';
7873  return;
7874  }
7875 
7876  // get number of digits for a text -> float -> text round-trip
7877  static constexpr auto d = std::numeric_limits<NumberType>::digits10;
7878 
7879  // the actual conversion
7880  const auto written_bytes =
7881  snprintf(m_buf.data(), m_buf.size(), "%.*g", d, x);
7882 
7883  // negative value indicates an error
7884  assert(written_bytes > 0);
7885  // check if buffer was large enough
7886  assert(static_cast<size_t>(written_bytes) < m_buf.size());
7887 
7888  // read information from locale
7889  const auto loc = localeconv();
7890  assert(loc != nullptr);
7891  const char thousands_sep =
7892  !loc->thousands_sep ? '\0' : loc->thousands_sep[0];
7893 
7894  const char decimal_point =
7895  !loc->decimal_point ? '\0' : loc->decimal_point[0];
7896 
7897  // erase thousands separator
7898  if (thousands_sep != '\0') {
7899  const auto end = std::remove(
7900  m_buf.begin(), m_buf.begin() + written_bytes, thousands_sep);
7901  std::fill(end, m_buf.end(), '\0');
7902  }
7903 
7904  // convert decimal point to '.'
7905  if (decimal_point != '\0' and decimal_point != '.') {
7906  for (auto& c : m_buf) {
7907  if (c == decimal_point) {
7908  c = '.';
7909  break;
7910  }
7911  }
7912  }
7913 
7914  // determine if need to append ".0"
7915  size_t i = 0;
7916  bool value_is_int_like = true;
7917  for (i = 0; i < m_buf.size(); ++i) {
7918  // break when end of number is reached
7919  if (m_buf[i] == '\0') {
7920  break;
7921  }
7922 
7923  // check if we find non-int character
7924  value_is_int_like = value_is_int_like and m_buf[i] != '.' and
7925  m_buf[i] != 'e' and m_buf[i] != 'E';
7926  }
7927 
7928  if (value_is_int_like) {
7929  // there must be 2 bytes left for ".0"
7930  assert((i + 2) < m_buf.size());
7931  // we write to the end of the number
7932  assert(m_buf[i] == '\0');
7933  assert(m_buf[i - 1] != '\0');
7934 
7935  // add ".0"
7936  m_buf[i] = '.';
7937  m_buf[i + 1] = '0';
7938 
7939  // the resulting string is properly terminated
7940  assert(m_buf[i + 2] == '\0');
7941  }
7942  }
7943  };

9024  static string_t to_unicode(const std::size_t codepoint1,
9025  const std::size_t codepoint2 = 0) {
9026  // calculate the code point from the given code points
9027  std::size_t codepoint = codepoint1;
9028 
9029  // check if codepoint1 is a high surrogate
9030  if (codepoint1 >= 0xD800 and codepoint1 <= 0xDBFF) {
9031  // check if codepoint2 is a low surrogate
9032  if (codepoint2 >= 0xDC00 and codepoint2 <= 0xDFFF) {
9033  codepoint =
9034  // high surrogate occupies the most significant 22 bits
9035  (codepoint1 << 10)
9036  // low surrogate occupies the least significant 15 bits
9037  + codepoint2
9038  // there is still the 0xD800, 0xDC00 and 0x10000 noise
9039  // in the result so we have to subtract with:
9040  // (0xD800 << 10) + DC00 - 0x10000 = 0x35FDC00
9041  - 0x35FDC00;
9042  } else {
9043  JSON_THROW(std::invalid_argument("missing or wrong low surrogate"));
9044  }
9045  }
9046 
9047  string_t result;
9048 
9049  if (codepoint < 0x80) {
9050  // 1-byte characters: 0xxxxxxx (ASCII)
9051  result.append(1, static_cast<typename string_t::value_type>(codepoint));
9052  } else if (codepoint <= 0x7ff) {
9053  // 2-byte characters: 110xxxxx 10xxxxxx
9054  result.append(1, static_cast<typename string_t::value_type>(
9055  0xC0 | ((codepoint >> 6) & 0x1F)));
9056  result.append(1, static_cast<typename string_t::value_type>(
9057  0x80 | (codepoint & 0x3F)));
9058  } else if (codepoint <= 0xffff) {
9059  // 3-byte characters: 1110xxxx 10xxxxxx 10xxxxxx
9060  result.append(1, static_cast<typename string_t::value_type>(
9061  0xE0 | ((codepoint >> 12) & 0x0F)));
9062  result.append(1, static_cast<typename string_t::value_type>(
9063  0x80 | ((codepoint >> 6) & 0x3F)));
9064  result.append(1, static_cast<typename string_t::value_type>(
9065  0x80 | (codepoint & 0x3F)));
9066  } else if (codepoint <= 0x10ffff) {
9067  // 4-byte characters: 11110xxx 10xxxxxx 10xxxxxx 10xxxxxx
9068  result.append(1, static_cast<typename string_t::value_type>(
9069  0xF0 | ((codepoint >> 18) & 0x07)));
9070  result.append(1, static_cast<typename string_t::value_type>(
9071  0x80 | ((codepoint >> 12) & 0x3F)));
9072  result.append(1, static_cast<typename string_t::value_type>(
9073  0x80 | ((codepoint >> 6) & 0x3F)));
9074  result.append(1, static_cast<typename string_t::value_type>(
9075  0x80 | (codepoint & 0x3F)));
9076  } else {
9077  JSON_THROW(std::out_of_range("code points above 0x10FFFF are invalid"));
9078  }
9079 
9080  return result;
9081  }

9841  goto basic_json_parser_71;
9842  }
9843  goto basic_json_parser_32;
9844  } else {
9845  if (yych <= 'F') {
9846  goto basic_json_parser_71;
9847  }
9848  if (yych <= '`') {
9849  goto basic_json_parser_32;
9850  }
9851  if (yych <= 'f') {
9852  goto basic_json_parser_71;
9853  }
9854  goto basic_json_parser_32;
9855  }
9856  basic_json_parser_66:
9857  yych = *++m_cursor;
9858  if (yych == 'e') {
9859  goto basic_json_parser_72;
9860  }
9861  goto basic_json_parser_32;
9862  basic_json_parser_67:

9866  break;
9867  }
9868  basic_json_parser_69:

9870  {
9871  last_token_type = token_type::literal_true;
9872  break;
9873  }
9874  basic_json_parser_71:
9875  ++m_cursor;
9876  if (m_limit <= m_cursor) {
9877  fill_line_buffer(1); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
9878  }
9879  yych = *m_cursor;
9880  if (yych <= '@') {
9881  if (yych <= '/') {

9883  }
9884  if (yych <= '9') {
9885  goto basic_json_parser_74;
9886  }
9887  goto basic_json_parser_32;
9888  } else {

9890  goto basic_json_parser_74;
9891  }
9892  if (yych <= '`') {
9893  goto basic_json_parser_32;
9894  }
9895  if (yych <= 'f') {
9896  goto basic_json_parser_74;
9897  }
9898  goto basic_json_parser_32;
9899  }
9900  basic_json_parser_72:
9901  ++m_cursor;
9902  {
9903  last_token_type = token_type::literal_false;
9904  break;
9905  }
9906  basic_json_parser_74:
9907  ++m_cursor;
9908  if (m_limit <= m_cursor) {

9912  if (yych <= '@') {

9915  }
9916  if (yych <= '9') {
9917  goto basic_json_parser_30;
9918  }

9920  } else {

9966  void fill_line_buffer(size_t n = 0) {
9967  // if line buffer is used, m_content points to its data
9968  assert(m_line_buffer.empty() or
9969  m_content ==
9970  reinterpret_cast<const lexer_char_t*>(m_line_buffer.data()));
9971 
9972  // if line buffer is used, m_limit is set past the end of its data
9973  assert(m_line_buffer.empty() or
9974  m_limit == m_content + m_line_buffer.size());
9975 
9976  // pointer relationships
9977  assert(m_content <= m_start);
9978  assert(m_start <= m_cursor);
9979  assert(m_cursor <= m_limit);
9980  assert(m_marker == nullptr or m_marker <= m_limit);
9981 
9982  // number of processed characters (p)
9983  const auto num_processed_chars = static_cast<size_t>(m_start - m_content);
9984  // offset for m_marker wrt. to m_start
9985  const auto offset_marker = (m_marker == nullptr) ? 0 : m_marker - m_start;
9986  // number of unprocessed characters (u)
9987  const auto offset_cursor = m_cursor - m_start;
9988 
9989  // no stream is used or end of file is reached
9990  if (m_stream == nullptr or m_stream->eof()) {
9991  // m_start may or may not be pointing into m_line_buffer at
9992  // this point. We trust the standard library to do the right
9993  // thing. See http://stackoverflow.com/q/28142011/266378
9994  m_line_buffer.assign(m_start, m_limit);
9995 
9996  // append n characters to make sure that there is sufficient
9997  // space between m_cursor and m_limit
9998  m_line_buffer.append(1, '\x00');
9999  if (n > 0) {
10000  m_line_buffer.append(n - 1, '\x01');
10001  }
10002  } else {
10003  // delete processed characters from line buffer
10004  m_line_buffer.erase(0, num_processed_chars);
10005  // read next line from input stream
10006  m_line_buffer_tmp.clear();
10007  std::getline(*m_stream, m_line_buffer_tmp, '\n');
10008 
10009  // add line with newline symbol to the line buffer
10010  m_line_buffer += m_line_buffer_tmp;
10011  m_line_buffer.push_back('\n');
10012  }
10013 
10014  // set pointers
10015  m_content = reinterpret_cast<const lexer_char_t*>(m_line_buffer.data());
10016  assert(m_content != nullptr);
10017  m_start = m_content;
10018  m_marker = m_start + offset_marker;
10019  m_cursor = m_start + offset_cursor;
10020  m_limit = m_start + m_line_buffer.size();
10021  }

10024  string_t get_token_string() const {
10025  assert(m_start != nullptr);
10026  return string_t(
10027  reinterpret_cast<typename string_t::const_pointer>(m_start),
10028  static_cast<size_t>(m_cursor - m_start));
10029  }
10030 
10088  string_t get_string() const {
10089  assert(m_cursor - m_start >= 2);
10090 
10091  string_t result;
10092  result.reserve(static_cast<size_t>(m_cursor - m_start - 2));
10093 
10094  // iterate the result between the quotes
10095  for (const lexer_char_t* i = m_start + 1; i < m_cursor - 1; ++i) {
10096  // find next escape character
10097  auto e = std::find(i, m_cursor - 1, '\\');
10098  if (e != i) {
10099  // see
10100  // https://github.com/nlohmann/json/issues/365#issuecomment-262874705
10101  for (auto k = i; k < e; k++) {
10102  result.push_back(static_cast<typename string_t::value_type>(*k));
10103  }
10104  i = e - 1; // -1 because of ++i
10105  } else {
10106  // processing escaped character
10107  // read next character
10108  ++i;
10109 
10110  switch (*i) {
10111  // the default escapes
10112  case 't': {
10113  result += "\t";
10114  break;
10115  }
10116  case 'b': {
10117  result += "\b";
10118  break;
10119  }
10120  case 'f': {
10121  result += "\f";
10122  break;
10123  }
10124  case 'n': {
10125  result += "\n";
10126  break;
10127  }
10128  case 'r': {
10129  result += "\r";
10130  break;
10131  }
10132  case '\\': {
10133  result += "\\";
10134  break;
10135  }
10136  case '/': {
10137  result += "/";
10138  break;
10139  }
10140  case '"': {
10141  result += "\"";
10142  break;
10143  }
10144 
10145  // unicode
10146  case 'u': {
10147  // get code xxxx from uxxxx
10148  auto codepoint = std::strtoul(
10149  std::string(
10150  reinterpret_cast<typename string_t::const_pointer>(i + 1),
10151  4)
10152  .c_str(),
10153  nullptr, 16);
10154 
10155  // check if codepoint is a high surrogate
10156  if (codepoint >= 0xD800 and codepoint <= 0xDBFF) {
10157  // make sure there is a subsequent unicode
10158  if ((i + 6 >= m_limit) or *(i + 5) != '\\' or *(i + 6) != 'u') {
10159  JSON_THROW(std::invalid_argument("missing low surrogate"));
10160  }
10161 
10162  // get code yyyy from uxxxx\uyyyy
10163  auto codepoint2 = std::strtoul(
10164  std::string(
10165  reinterpret_cast<typename string_t::const_pointer>(i +
10166  7),
10167  4)
10168  .c_str(),
10169  nullptr, 16);
10170  result += to_unicode(codepoint, codepoint2);
10171  // skip the next 10 characters (xxxx\uyyyy)
10172  i += 10;
10173  } else if (codepoint >= 0xDC00 and codepoint <= 0xDFFF) {
10174  // we found a lone low surrogate
10175  JSON_THROW(std::invalid_argument("missing high surrogate"));
10176  } else {
10177  // add unicode character(s)
10178  result += to_unicode(codepoint);
10179  // skip the next four characters (xxxx)
10180  i += 4;
10181  }
10182  break;
10183  }
10184  }
10185  }
10186  }
10187 
10188  return result;
10189  }

10201  public:

10211  template <typename T, typename = typename std::enable_if<
10212  std::is_arithmetic<T>::value>::type>
10213  bool to(T& val) const {
10214  return parse(val, std::is_integral<T>());
10215  }
10216 
10217  private:
10218  const char* const m_start = nullptr;
10219  const char* const m_end = nullptr;
10220 
10221  // floating-point conversion
10222 
10223  // overloaded wrappers for strtod/strtof/strtold
10224  // that will be called from parse<floating_point_t>
10225  static void strtof(float& f, const char* str, char** endptr) {
10226  f = std::strtof(str, endptr);
10227  }
10228 
10229  static void strtof(double& f, const char* str, char** endptr) {
10230  f = std::strtod(str, endptr);
10231  }
10232

10234  f = std::strtold(str, endptr);

10236 
10237  template <typename T>
10238  bool parse(T& value, /*is_integral=*/std::false_type) const {
10239  // replace decimal separator with locale-specific version,
10240  // when necessary; data will point to either the original
10241  // string, or buf, or tempstr containing the fixed string.
10242  std::string tempstr;
10243  std::array<char, 64> buf;
10244  const size_t len = static_cast<size_t>(m_end - m_start);
10245 
10246  // lexer will reject empty numbers
10247  assert(len > 0);
10248 
10249  // since dealing with strtod family of functions, we're
10250  // getting the decimal point char from the C locale facilities
10251  // instead of C++'s numpunct facet of the current std::locale
10252  const auto loc = localeconv();
10253  assert(loc != nullptr);
10254  const char decimal_point_char =
10255  (loc->decimal_point == nullptr) ? '.' : loc->decimal_point[0];
10256 
10257  const char* data = m_start;
10258 
10259  if (decimal_point_char != '.') {
10260  const size_t ds_pos =
10261  static_cast<size_t>(std::find(m_start, m_end, '.') - m_start);
10262 
10263  if (ds_pos != len) {
10264  // copy the data into the local buffer or tempstr, if
10265  // buffer is too small; replace decimal separator, and
10266  // update data to point to the modified bytes
10267  if ((len + 1) < buf.size()) {
10268  std::copy(m_start, m_end, buf.begin());
10269  buf[len] = 0;
10270  buf[ds_pos] = decimal_point_char;
10271  data = buf.data();
10272  } else {
10273  tempstr.assign(m_start, m_end);
10274  tempstr[ds_pos] = decimal_point_char;
10275  data = tempstr.c_str();
10276  }
10277  }
10278  }
10279 
10280  char* endptr = nullptr;
10281  value = 0;
10282  // this calls appropriate overload depending on T
10283  strtof(value, data, &endptr);
10284 
10285  // parsing was successful iff strtof parsed exactly the number
10286  // of characters determined by the lexer (len)
10287  const bool ok = (endptr == (data + len));
10288 
10289  if (ok and (value == static_cast<T>(0.0)) and (*data == '-')) {
10290  // some implementations forget to negate the zero
10291  value = -0.0;
10292  }
10293 
10294  return ok;
10295  }
10296 
10297  // integral conversion
10298 
10299  signed long long parse_integral(char** endptr,
10300  /*is_signed*/ std::true_type) const {
10301  return std::strtoll(m_start, endptr, 10);
10302  }
10303 
10304  unsigned long long parse_integral(char** endptr,
10305  /*is_signed*/ std::false_type) const {
10306  return std::strtoull(m_start, endptr, 10);
10307  }
10308 
10309  template <typename T>
10310  bool parse(T& value, /*is_integral=*/std::true_type) const {
10311  char* endptr = nullptr;
10312  errno = 0; // these are thread-local
10313  const auto x = parse_integral(&endptr, std::is_signed<T>());
10314 
10315  // called right overload?
10316  static_assert(std::is_signed<T>() == std::is_signed<decltype(x)>(), "");
10317 
10318  value = static_cast<T>(x);
10319 
10320  return (x ==
10321  static_cast<decltype(x)>(value)) // x fits into destination T
10322  and (x < 0) == (value < 0) // preserved sign
10323  // and ((x != 0) or is_integral()) // strto[u]ll did nto
10324  // fail
10325  and (errno == 0) // strto[u]ll did not overflow
10326  and (m_start < m_end) // token was not empty
10327  and (endptr == m_end); // parsed entire token exactly
10328  }
10329  };

10350  bool get_number(basic_json& result, const token_type token) const {
10351  assert(m_start != nullptr);
10352  assert(m_start < m_cursor);
10353  assert((token == token_type::value_unsigned) or
10354  (token == token_type::value_integer) or
10355  (token == token_type::value_float));
10356 
10357  strtonum num_converter(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(m_start),
10358  reinterpret_cast<const char*>(m_cursor));
10359 
10360  switch (token) {
10361  case lexer::token_type::value_unsigned: {
10362  number_unsigned_t val;
10363  if (num_converter.to(val)) {
10364  // parsing successful
10365  result.m_type = value_t::number_unsigned;
10366  result.m_value = val;
10367  return true;
10368  }
10369  break;
10370  }
10371 
10372  case lexer::token_type::value_integer: {
10373  number_integer_t val;
10374  if (num_converter.to(val)) {
10375  // parsing successful
10376  result.m_type = value_t::number_integer;
10377  result.m_value = val;
10378  return true;
10379  }
10380  break;
10381  }
10382 
10383  default: { break; }
10384  }
10385 
10386  // parse float (either explicitly or because a previous conversion
10387  // failed)
10388  number_float_t val;
10389  if (num_converter.to(val)) {
10390  // parsing successful
10391  result.m_type = value_t::number_float;
10392  result.m_value = val;
10393 
10394  // replace infinity and NAN by null
10395  if (not std::isfinite(result.m_value.number_float)) {
10396  result.m_type = value_t::null;
10397  result.m_value = basic_json::json_value();
10398  }
10399 
10400  return true;
10401  }
10402 
10403  // couldn't parse number in any format
10404  return false;
10405  }

10461  // read first token
10462  get_token();
10463 
10464  basic_json result = parse_internal(true);
10465  result.assert_invariant();
10466 
10467  expect(lexer::token_type::end_of_input);
10468 
10469  // return parser result and replace it with null in case the
10470  // top-level value was discarded by the callback function
10471  return result.is_discarded() ? basic_json() : std::move(result);
10472  }

10474  private:
10476  basic_json parse_internal(bool keep) {
10477  auto result = basic_json(value_t::discarded);
10478 
10479  switch (last_token) {
10480  case lexer::token_type::begin_object: {
10481  if (keep and (not callback or
10482  ((keep = callback(depth++, parse_event_t::object_start,
10483  result)) != 0))) {
10484  // explicitly set result to object to cope with {}
10485  result.m_type = value_t::object;
10486  result.m_value = value_t::object;
10487  }
10488 
10489  // read next token
10490  get_token();
10491 
10492  // closing } -> we are done
10493  if (last_token == lexer::token_type::end_object) {
10494  get_token();
10495  if (keep and callback and
10496  not callback(--depth, parse_event_t::object_end, result)) {
10497  result = basic_json(value_t::discarded);
10498  }
10499  return result;
10500  }
10501 
10502  // no comma is expected here
10503  unexpect(lexer::token_type::value_separator);
10504 
10505  // otherwise: parse key-value pairs
10506  do {
10507  // ugly, but could be fixed with loop reorganization
10508  if (last_token == lexer::token_type::value_separator) {
10509  get_token();
10510  }
10511 
10512  // store key
10513  expect(lexer::token_type::value_string);
10514  const auto key = m_lexer.get_string();
10515 
10516  bool keep_tag = false;
10517  if (keep) {
10518  if (callback) {
10519  basic_json k(key);
10520  keep_tag = callback(depth, parse_event_t::key, k);
10521  } else {
10522  keep_tag = true;
10523  }
10524  }
10525 
10526  // parse separator (:)
10527  get_token();
10528  expect(lexer::token_type::name_separator);
10529 
10530  // parse and add value
10531  get_token();
10532  auto value = parse_internal(keep);
10533  if (keep and keep_tag and not value.is_discarded()) {
10534  result[key] = std::move(value);
10535  }
10536  } while (last_token == lexer::token_type::value_separator);
10537 
10538  // closing }
10539  expect(lexer::token_type::end_object);
10540  get_token();
10541  if (keep and callback and
10542  not callback(--depth, parse_event_t::object_end, result)) {
10543  result = basic_json(value_t::discarded);
10544  }
10545 
10546  return result;
10547  }
10548 
10549  case lexer::token_type::begin_array: {
10550  if (keep and (not callback or
10551  ((keep = callback(depth++, parse_event_t::array_start,
10552  result)) != 0))) {
10553  // explicitly set result to object to cope with []
10554  result.m_type = value_t::array;
10555  result.m_value = value_t::array;
10556  }
10557 
10558  // read next token
10559  get_token();
10560 
10561  // closing ] -> we are done
10562  if (last_token == lexer::token_type::end_array) {
10563  get_token();
10564  if (callback and
10565  not callback(--depth, parse_event_t::array_end, result)) {
10566  result = basic_json(value_t::discarded);
10567  }
10568  return result;
10569  }
10570 
10571  // no comma is expected here
10572  unexpect(lexer::token_type::value_separator);
10573 
10574  // otherwise: parse values
10575  do {
10576  // ugly, but could be fixed with loop reorganization
10577  if (last_token == lexer::token_type::value_separator) {
10578  get_token();
10579  }
10580 
10581  // parse value
10582  auto value = parse_internal(keep);
10583  if (keep and not value.is_discarded()) {
10584  result.push_back(std::move(value));
10585  }
10586  } while (last_token == lexer::token_type::value_separator);
10587 
10588  // closing ]
10589  expect(lexer::token_type::end_array);
10590  get_token();
10591  if (keep and callback and
10592  not callback(--depth, parse_event_t::array_end, result)) {
10593  result = basic_json(value_t::discarded);
10594  }
10595 
10596  return result;
10597  }
10598 
10599  case lexer::token_type::literal_null: {
10600  get_token();
10601  result.m_type = value_t::null;
10602  break;
10603  }
10604 
10605  case lexer::token_type::value_string: {
10606  const auto s = m_lexer.get_string();
10607  get_token();
10608  result = basic_json(s);
10609  break;
10610  }
10611 
10612  case lexer::token_type::literal_true: {
10613  get_token();
10614  result.m_type = value_t::boolean;
10615  result.m_value = true;
10616  break;
10617  }
10618 
10619  case lexer::token_type::literal_false: {
10620  get_token();
10621  result.m_type = value_t::boolean;
10622  result.m_value = false;
10623  break;
10624  }
10625 
10626  case lexer::token_type::value_unsigned:
10627  case lexer::token_type::value_integer:
10628  case lexer::token_type::value_float: {
10629  m_lexer.get_number(result, last_token);
10630  get_token();
10631  break;
10632  }
10633 
10634  default: {
10635  // the last token was unexpected
10636  unexpect(last_token);
10637  }
10638  }
10639 
10640  if (keep and callback and
10641  not callback(depth, parse_event_t::value, result)) {
10642  result = basic_json(value_t::discarded);
10643  }
10644  return result;
10645  }

10653  void expect(typename lexer::token_type t) const {
10654  if (t != last_token) {
10655  std::string error_msg = "parse error - unexpected ";
10656  error_msg += (last_token == lexer::token_type::parse_error
10657  ? ("'" + m_lexer.get_token_string() + "'")
10658  : lexer::token_type_name(last_token));
10659  error_msg += "; expected " + lexer::token_type_name(t);
10660  JSON_THROW(std::invalid_argument(error_msg));
10661  }
10662  }

10665  if (t == last_token) {
10666  std::string error_msg = "parse error - unexpected ";
10667  error_msg += (last_token == lexer::token_type::parse_error
10668  ? ("'" + m_lexer.get_token_string() + "'")
10669  : lexer::token_type_name(last_token));
10670  JSON_THROW(std::invalid_argument(error_msg));
10671  }
10672  }

10783  reference get_and_create(reference j) const {
10784  pointer result = &j;
10785 
10786  // in case no reference tokens exist, return a reference to the
10787  // JSON value j which will be overwritten by a primitive value
10788  for (const auto& reference_token : reference_tokens) {
10789  switch (result->m_type) {
10790  case value_t::null: {
10791  if (reference_token == "0") {
10792  // start a new array if reference token is 0
10793  result = &result->operator[](0);
10794  } else {
10795  // start a new object otherwise
10796  result = &result->operator[](reference_token);
10797  }
10798  break;
10799  }
10800 
10801  case value_t::object: {
10802  // create an entry in the object
10803  result = &result->operator[](reference_token);
10804  break;
10805  }
10806 
10807  case value_t::array: {
10808  // create an entry in the array
10809  result = &result->operator[](static_cast<size_type>(
10810  nlohmann::std_support::stoi(reference_token)));
10811  break;
10812  }
10813 
10814  /*
10815  The following code is only reached if there exists a
10816  reference token _and_ the current value is primitive. In
10817  this case, we have an error situation, because primitive
10818  values may only occur as single value; that is, with an
10819  empty list of reference tokens.
10820  */
10821  default: {
10822  JSON_THROW(std::domain_error("invalid value to unflatten"));
10823  }
10824  }
10825  }
10826 
10827  return *result;
10828  }
10829 
10849  reference get_unchecked(pointer ptr) const {
10850  for (const auto& reference_token : reference_tokens) {
10851  // convert null values to arrays or objects before continuing
10852  if (ptr->m_type == value_t::null) {
10853  // check if reference token is a number
10854  const bool nums =
10855  std::all_of(reference_token.begin(), reference_token.end(),
10856  [](const char x) { return std::isdigit(x); });
10857 
10858  // change value to array for numbers or "-" or to object
10859  // otherwise
10860  if (nums or reference_token == "-") {
10861  *ptr = value_t::array;
10862  } else {
10863  *ptr = value_t::object;
10864  }
10865  }
10866 
10867  switch (ptr->m_type) {
10868  case value_t::object: {
10869  // use unchecked object access
10870  ptr = &ptr->operator[](reference_token);
10871  break;
10872  }
10873 
10874  case value_t::array: {
10875  // error condition (cf. RFC 6901, Sect. 4)
10876  if (reference_token.size() > 1 and reference_token[0] == '0') {
10877  JSON_THROW(
10878  std::domain_error("array index must not begin with '0'"));
10879  }
10880 
10881  if (reference_token == "-") {
10882  // explicitly treat "-" as index beyond the end
10883  ptr = &ptr->operator[](ptr->m_value.array->size());
10884  } else {
10885  // convert array index to number; unchecked access
10886  ptr = &ptr->operator[](static_cast<size_type>(
10887  nlohmann::std_support::stoi(reference_token)));
10888  }
10889  break;
10890  }
10891 
10892  default: {
10893  JSON_THROW(std::out_of_range("unresolved reference token '" +
10894  reference_token + "'"));
10895  }
10896  }
10897  }
10898 
10899  return *ptr;
10900  }
10901 
10902  reference get_checked(pointer ptr) const {
10903  for (const auto& reference_token : reference_tokens) {
10904  switch (ptr->m_type) {
10905  case value_t::object: {
10906  // note: at performs range check
10907  ptr = &ptr->at(reference_token);
10908  break;
10909  }
10910 
10911  case value_t::array: {
10912  if (reference_token == "-") {
10913  // "-" always fails the range check
10914  JSON_THROW(std::out_of_range(
10915  "array index '-' (" +
10916  nlohmann::std_support::to_string(ptr->m_value.array->size()) +
10917  ") is out of range"));
10918  }
10919 
10920  // error condition (cf. RFC 6901, Sect. 4)
10921  if (reference_token.size() > 1 and reference_token[0] == '0') {
10922  JSON_THROW(
10923  std::domain_error("array index must not begin with '0'"));
10924  }
10925 
10926  // note: at performs range check
10927  ptr = &ptr->at(static_cast<size_type>(
10928  nlohmann::std_support::stoi(reference_token)));
10929  break;
10930  }
10931 
10932  default: {
10933  JSON_THROW(std::out_of_range("unresolved reference token '" +
10934  reference_token + "'"));
10935  }
10936  }
10937  }

11031  static std::vector<std::string> split(const std::string& reference_string) {
11032  std::vector<std::string> result;
11033 
11034  // special case: empty reference string -> no reference tokens
11035  if (reference_string.empty()) {
11036  return result;
11037  }
11038 
11039  // check if nonempty reference string begins with slash
11040  if (reference_string[0] != '/') {
11041  JSON_THROW(
11042  std::domain_error("JSON pointer must be empty or begin with '/'"));
11043  }
11044 
11045  // extract the reference tokens:
11046  // - slash: position of the last read slash (or end of string)
11047  // - start: position after the previous slash
11048  for (
11049  // search for the first slash after the first character
11050  size_t slash = reference_string.find_first_of('/', 1),
11051  // set the beginning of the first reference token
11052  start = 1;
11053  // we can stop if start == string::npos+1 = 0
11054  start != 0;
11055  // set the beginning of the next reference token
11056  // (will eventually be 0 if slash == std::string::npos)
11057  start = slash + 1,
11058  // find next slash
11059  slash = reference_string.find_first_of('/', start)) {
11060  // use the text between the beginning of the reference token
11061  // (start) and the last slash (slash).
11062  auto reference_token = reference_string.substr(start, slash - start);
11063 
11064  // check reference tokens are properly escaped
11065  for (size_t pos = reference_token.find_first_of('~');
11066  pos != std::string::npos;
11067  pos = reference_token.find_first_of('~', pos + 1)) {
11068  assert(reference_token[pos] == '~');
11069 
11070  // ~ must be followed by 0 or 1
11071  if (pos == reference_token.size() - 1 or
11072  (reference_token[pos + 1] != '0' and
11073  reference_token[pos + 1] != '1')) {
11074  JSON_THROW(std::domain_error(
11075  "escape error: '~' must be followed with '0' or '1'"));
11076  }
11077  }
11078 
11079  // finally, store the reference token
11080  unescape(reference_token);
11081  result.push_back(reference_token);
11082  }
11083 
11084  return result;
11085  }
11086 
11087  private:
11100  static void replace_substring(std::string& s, const std::string& f,
11101  const std::string& t) {
11102  assert(not f.empty());
11103 
11104  for (size_t pos = s.find(f); // find first occurrence of f
11105  pos != std::string::npos; // make sure f was found
11106  s.replace(pos, f.size(), t), // replace with t
11107  pos = s.find(f, pos + t.size()) // find next occurrence of f
11108  )
11109  ;
11110  }
11111 
11113  static std::string escape(std::string s) {
11114  // escape "~"" to "~0" and "/" to "~1"
11115  replace_substring(s, "~", "~0");
11116  replace_substring(s, "/", "~1");
11117  return s;
11118  }
11119 
11121  static void unescape(std::string& s) {
11122  // first transform any occurrence of the sequence '~1' to '/'
11123  replace_substring(s, "~1", "/");
11124  // then transform any occurrence of the sequence '~0' to '~'
11125  replace_substring(s, "~0", "~");
11126  }

11135  static void flatten(const std::string& reference_string,
11136  const basic_json& value, basic_json& result) {
11137  switch (value.m_type) {
11138  case value_t::array: {
11139  if (value.m_value.array->empty()) {
11140  // flatten empty array as null
11141  result[reference_string] = nullptr;
11142  } else {
11143  // iterate array and use index as reference string
11144  for (size_t i = 0; i < value.m_value.array->size(); ++i) {
11145  flatten(
11146  reference_string + "/" + nlohmann::std_support::to_string(i),
11147  value.m_value.array->operator[](i), result);
11148  }
11149  }
11150  break;
11151  }
11152 
11153  case value_t::object: {
11154  if (value.m_value.object->empty()) {
11155  // flatten empty object as null
11156  result[reference_string] = nullptr;
11157  } else {
11158  // iterate object and use keys as reference string
11159  for (const auto& element : *value.m_value.object) {
11160  flatten(reference_string + "/" + escape(element.first),
11161  element.second, result);
11162  }
11163  }
11164  break;
11165  }
11166 
11167  default: {
11168  // add primitive value with its reference string
11169  result[reference_string] = value;
11170  break;
11171  }
11172  }
11173  }
11174 
11180  static basic_json unflatten(const basic_json& value) {
11181  if (not value.is_object()) {
11182  JSON_THROW(std::domain_error("only objects can be unflattened"));
11183  }
11184 
11185  basic_json result;
11186 
11187  // iterate the JSON object values
11188  for (const auto& element : *value.m_value.object) {
11189  if (not element.second.is_primitive()) {
11190  JSON_THROW(std::domain_error("values in object must be primitive"));
11191  }
11192 
11193  // assign value to reference pointed to by JSON pointer; Note
11194  // that if the JSON pointer is "" (i.e., points to the whole
11195  // value), function get_and_create returns a reference to
11196  // result itself. An assignment will then create a primitive
11197  // value.
11198  json_pointer(element.first).get_and_create(result) = element.second;
11199  }
11200 
11201  return result;
11202  }
