11400 
11437  basic_json patch(const basic_json& json_patch) const {
11438  // make a working copy to apply the patch to
11439  basic_json result = *this;
11440 
11441  // the valid JSON Patch operations
11442  enum class patch_operations {
11443  add,
11444  remove,
11445  replace,
11446  move,
11447  copy,
11448  test,
11449  invalid
11450  };
11451 
11452  const auto get_op = [](const std::string op) {
11453  if (op == "add") {
11454  return patch_operations::add;
11455  }
11456  if (op == "remove") {
11457  return patch_operations::remove;
11458  }
11459  if (op == "replace") {
11460  return patch_operations::replace;
11461  }
11462  if (op == "move") {
11463  return patch_operations::move;
11464  }
11465  if (op == "copy") {
11466  return patch_operations::copy;
11467  }
11468  if (op == "test") {
11469  return patch_operations::test;
11470  }
11471 
11472  return patch_operations::invalid;
11473  };
11474 
11475  // wrapper for "add" operation; add value at ptr
11476  const auto operation_add = [&result](json_pointer& ptr, basic_json val) {
11477  // adding to the root of the target document means replacing it
11478  if (ptr.is_root()) {
11479  result = val;
11480  } else {
11481  // make sure the top element of the pointer exists
11482  json_pointer top_pointer = ptr.top();
11483  if (top_pointer != ptr) {
11484  result.at(top_pointer);
11485  }
11486 
11487  // get reference to parent of JSON pointer ptr
11488  const auto last_path = ptr.pop_back();
11489  basic_json& parent = result[ptr];
11490 
11491  switch (parent.m_type) {
11492  case value_t::null:
11493  case value_t::object: {
11494  // use operator[] to add value
11495  parent[last_path] = val;
11496  break;
11497  }
11498 
11499  case value_t::array: {
11500  if (last_path == "-") {
11501  // special case: append to back
11502  parent.push_back(val);
11503  } else {
11504  const auto idx = nlohmann::std_support::stoi(last_path);
11505  if (static_cast<size_type>(idx) > parent.size()) {
11506  // avoid undefined behavior
11507  JSON_THROW(std::out_of_range(
11508  "array index " + nlohmann::std_support::to_string(idx) +
11509  " is out of range"));
11510  } else {
11511  // default case: insert add offset
11512  parent.insert(
11513  parent.begin() + static_cast<difference_type>(idx), val);
11514  }
11515  }
11516  break;
11517  }
11518 
11519  default: {
11520  // if there exists a parent it cannot be primitive
11521  assert(false); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
11522  }
11523  }
11524  }
11525  };
11526 
11527  // wrapper for "remove" operation; remove value at ptr
11528  const auto operation_remove = [&result](json_pointer& ptr) {
11529  // get reference to parent of JSON pointer ptr
11530  const auto last_path = ptr.pop_back();
11531  basic_json& parent = result.at(ptr);
11532 
11533  // remove child
11534  if (parent.is_object()) {
11535  // perform range check
11536  auto it = parent.find(last_path);
11537  if (it != parent.end()) {
11538  parent.erase(it);
11539  } else {
11540  JSON_THROW(std::out_of_range("key '" + last_path + "' not found"));
11541  }
11542  } else if (parent.is_array()) {
11543  // note erase performs range check
11544  parent.erase(
11545  static_cast<size_type>(nlohmann::std_support::stoi(last_path)));
11546  }
11547  };
11548 
11549  // type check
11550  if (not json_patch.is_array()) {
11551  // a JSON patch must be an array of objects
11552  JSON_THROW(
11553  std::invalid_argument("JSON patch must be an array of objects"));
11554  }
11555 
11556  // iterate and apply the operations
11557  for (const auto& val : json_patch) {
11558  // wrapper to get a value for an operation
11559  const auto get_value = [&val](const std::string& op,
11560  const std::string& member,
11561  bool string_type) -> basic_json& {
11562  // find value
11563  auto it = val.m_value.object->find(member);
11564 
11565  // context-sensitive error message
11566  const auto error_msg =
11567  (op == "op") ? "operation" : "operation '" + op + "'";
11568 
11569  // check if desired value is present
11570  if (it == val.m_value.object->end()) {
11571  JSON_THROW(std::invalid_argument(error_msg + " must have member '" +
11572  member + "'"));
11573  }
11574 
11575  // check if result is of type string
11576  if (string_type and not it->second.is_string()) {
11577  JSON_THROW(std::invalid_argument(
11578  error_msg + " must have string member '" + member + "'"));
11579  }
11580 
11581  // no error: return value
11582  return it->second;
11583  };
11584 
11585  // type check
11586  if (not val.is_object()) {
11587  JSON_THROW(
11588  std::invalid_argument("JSON patch must be an array of objects"));
11589  }
11590 
11591  // collect mandatory members
11592  const std::string op = get_value("op", "op", true);
11593  const std::string path = get_value(op, "path", true);
11594  json_pointer ptr(path);
11595 
11596  switch (get_op(op)) {
11597  case patch_operations::add: {
11598  operation_add(ptr, get_value("add", "value", false));
11599  break;
11600  }
11601 
11602  case patch_operations::remove: {
11603  operation_remove(ptr);
11604  break;
11605  }
11606 
11607  case patch_operations::replace: {
11608  // the "path" location must exist - use at()
11609  result.at(ptr) = get_value("replace", "value", false);
11610  break;
11611  }
11612 
11613  case patch_operations::move: {
11614  const std::string from_path = get_value("move", "from", true);
11615  json_pointer from_ptr(from_path);
11616 
11617  // the "from" location must exist - use at()
11618  basic_json v = result.at(from_ptr);
11619 
11620  // The move operation is functionally identical to a
11621  // "remove" operation on the "from" location, followed
11622  // immediately by an "add" operation at the target
11623  // location with the value that was just removed.
11624  operation_remove(from_ptr);
11625  operation_add(ptr, v);
11626  break;
11627  }
11628 
11629  case patch_operations::copy: {
11630  const std::string from_path = get_value("copy", "from", true);
11631  ;
11632  const json_pointer from_ptr(from_path);
11633 
11634  // the "from" location must exist - use at()
11635  result[ptr] = result.at(from_ptr);
11636  break;
11637  }
11638 
11639  case patch_operations::test: {
11640  bool success = false;
11641  JSON_TRY {
11642  // check if "value" matches the one at "path"
11643  // the "path" location must exist - use at()
11644  success = (result.at(ptr) == get_value("test", "value", false));
11645  }
11646  JSON_CATCH(std::out_of_range&) {
11647  // ignore out of range errors: success remains false
11648  }
11649 
11650  // throw an exception if test fails
11651  if (not success) {
11652  JSON_THROW(std::domain_error("unsuccessful: " + val.dump()));
11653  }
11654 
11655  break;
11656  }
11657 
11658  case patch_operations::invalid: {
11659  // op must be "add", "remove", "replace", "move", "copy", or
11660  // "test"
11661  JSON_THROW(
11662  std::invalid_argument("operation value '" + op + "' is invalid"));
11663  }
11664  }
11665  }
11666 
11667  return result;
11668  }
11669 
11702  static basic_json diff(const basic_json& source, const basic_json& target,
11703  const std::string& path = "") {
11704  // the patch
11705  basic_json result(value_t::array);
11706 
11707  // if the values are the same, return empty patch
11708  if (source == target) {
11709  return result;
11710  }
11711 
11712  if (source.type() != target.type()) {
11713  // different types: replace value
11714  result.push_back({{"op", "replace"}, {"path", path}, {"value", target}});
11715  } else {
11716  switch (source.type()) {
11717  case value_t::array: {
11718  // first pass: traverse common elements
11719  size_t i = 0;
11720  while (i < source.size() and i < target.size()) {
11721  // recursive call to compare array values at index i
11722  auto temp_diff =
11723  diff(source[i], target[i],
11724  path + "/" + nlohmann::std_support::to_string(i));
11725  result.insert(result.end(), temp_diff.begin(), temp_diff.end());
11726  ++i;
11727  }
11728 
11729  // i now reached the end of at least one array
11730  // in a second pass, traverse the remaining elements
11731 
11732  // remove my remaining elements
11733  const auto end_index = static_cast<difference_type>(result.size());
11734  while (i < source.size()) {
11735  // add operations in reverse order to avoid invalid
11736  // indices
11737  result.insert(
11738  result.begin() + end_index,
11739  object({{"op", "remove"},
11740  {"path",
11741  path + "/" + nlohmann::std_support::to_string(i)}}));
11742  ++i;
11743  }
11744 
11745  // add other remaining elements
11746  while (i < target.size()) {
11747  result.push_back(
11748  {{"op", "add"},
11749  {"path", path + "/" + nlohmann::std_support::to_string(i)},
11750  {"value", target[i]}});
11751  ++i;
11752  }
11753 
11754  break;
11755  }
11756 
11757  case value_t::object: {
11758  // first pass: traverse this object's elements
11759  for (auto it = source.begin(); it != source.end(); ++it) {
11760  // escape the key name to be used in a JSON patch
11761  const auto key = json_pointer::escape(it.key());
11762 
11763  if (target.find(it.key()) != target.end()) {
11764  // recursive call to compare object values at key it
11765  auto temp_diff =
11766  diff(it.value(), target[it.key()], path + "/" + key);
11767  result.insert(result.end(), temp_diff.begin(), temp_diff.end());
11768  } else {
11769  // found a key that is not in o -> remove it
11770  result.push_back(
11771  object({{"op", "remove"}, {"path", path + "/" + key}}));
11772  }
11773  }
11774 
11775  // second pass: traverse other object's elements
11776  for (auto it = target.begin(); it != target.end(); ++it) {
11777  if (source.find(it.key()) == source.end()) {
11778  // found a key that is not in this -> add it
11779  const auto key = json_pointer::escape(it.key());
11780  result.push_back({{"op", "add"},
11781  {"path", path + "/" + key},
11782  {"value", it.value()}});
11783  }
11784  }
11785 
11786  break;
11787  }
11788 
11789  default: {
11790  // both primitive type: replace value
11791  result.push_back(
11792  {{"op", "replace"}, {"path", path}, {"value", target}});
11793  break;
11794  }
11795  }
11796  }
11797 
11798  return result;
11799  }
11800 
11802 };
